# Specify desired highlighting theme (e.g. "TwoDark"). Run `bat --list-themes`
# for a list of all available themes

# NOTE: Reason for changing theme.
#
# By the following pr, when the appearance of macos is light mode,
# the default theme of bat is "Monokai Extended Light".
#
#   https://github.com/sharkdp/bat/pull/2197
#
# If the background color of the terminal is black,
# "Monokai Extended Light" theme makes the font color difficult to see.
--theme="Visual Studio Dark+"
